caption:
Starting over in a new country is hard. But it’s possible when barriers are lifted and you’re welcomed into a supportive community.

Read the full quote from one of our Women Lead Job Readiness graduates:

“I’m a physician in my country, so I have a degree in general medicine. It’s hard to be here because we have to start over, but I have received help from the Immigrant Welcome Center to eliminate barriers and achieve my goals. It’s hard to start, but it is possible, and I hope so that I will be better.”
